Don’t make plans for Saturday and Sunday. Stay in and binge-watch DStv Premium, including all the SuperSport channels. For the weekend of 14-15 March, DStv customers on any package* will be able to livestream all the DStv channels through the DStv Now app. That means customers on EasyView, Access, Family, Compact and Compact Plus will be able to watch every live channel on the DStv Premium bouquet, using DStv Now. * Indian, French and Portuguese language packages not included.  <img class="aligncenter wp-image-381391" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DStv-Now-open-weekend.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="335" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DStv-Now-open-weekend.jpg 1200w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DStv-Now-open-weekend-300x157.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DStv-Now-open-weekend-1024x536.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DStv-Now-open-weekend-768x402.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Here are our picks for which sports events to watch, live: Sunday 15 March: Australia vs New Zealand 2nd ODI, 1:20 to 9:45 on SS2 Sunday 15 March: India vs South Africa 2nd ODI, 9:45 to 18:30 on SS2 Saturday 14 March: The Players Championship Day 3, 20:00 to 1:00 on SS5 Sunday 15 March: The Players Championship Day 4, 19:00 to 0:00 on SS5 Saturday 14 March: Vodacom Super Rugby, Blues vs Emirates Lions, 5:20 to 7:30 on SS1 Saturday 14 March: Vodacom Super Rugby, Reds vs Vodacom Bulls, 10:10 to 12:30 on SS1 Saturday 14 March: Vodacom Super Rugby, Cell C Sharks vs DHL Stormers, 15:00 to 17:20 on SS1 Saturday 14 March: Six Nations, Wales vs Scotland, 16:10 to 18:15 on SS5 Sunday 15 March: Vodacom Super Rugby, Brumbies vs Waratahs, 7:00 to 9:00 SS1 Saturday 14 March: EFC 84 – Welterweight Title Fight, Themba Gorimbo vs Lyle Karam